OL,7,FThe Home Office can then give a
OL,8,Freasonable grounds decision, if it is
OL,9,Fsuspected but not proved that someone
OL,10,Fis a victim of modern slavery, or a
OL,11,Fconclusive grounds decision, where the
OL,12,Fauthority considers it 'more likely
OL,13,Fthan not' that the person has been a
OL,14,Fvictim of modern slavery. This means
OL,15,Fthey are then eligible for further
OL,16,Fhousing, health and legal support.
OL,18,FWhile Rohima received a reasonable
OL,19,Fgrounds decision quickly, she is still
OL,20,Fwaiting for the final decision on her
OL,21,Fcase.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/14
