OL,7,FDespite her harrowing experience,
OL,8,FRohima said she looking to the future:
OL,9,F"I (try) to forget, but sometimes in
OL,10,Fthe night, it's like (a) nightmare.
OL,12,F"My body also like shaking, afraid of
OL,13,Fthose things that happened to me. I
OL,14,Fhad complex PTSD but I'm getting more
OL,15,Fwell. How I was before, is totally
OL,16,Fdifferent.
OL,18,F"When I (came) here I didn't think I
OL,19,Fhad a future, but I can now think
OL,20,Fabout this hope I have."
